The paper focuses on improving the performance of deep neural networks through the use of a new activation function and weight initialization method. This falls under the category of neural networks (cs.NE) and machine learning (cs.LG). The experiments conducted in the paper involve image classification tasks, which suggests that computer vision (cs.CV) is also a likely sub-category. Additionally, the paper discusses the use of the proposed methods for natural language processing tasks, indicating that artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and computational linguistics (cs.CL) are also possible sub-categories.
